-- Argentine Stocks: Banco Hipotecario, Petrobras Argentina and YPF
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-01-17T16:04:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/argentine-stocks-banco-hipotecario-petrobras-argentina-and-ypf.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1 p.m. in Buenos Aires.  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index rose 1.1 percent to 2,785.04.  Banco Hipotecario SA (BHIP)   advanced 2.4 percent to 1.73
pesos. The Argentine lender rose in line with global stocks on
bets that slowing growth in China will lead to easing monetary
policy.  YPF SA (YPFD)   gained 4 percent to 171 pesos. Raymond
James reiterated an “outperform” recommendation for
Argentina’s largest oil company after it increased diesel prices
in the country between 2 percent and 4 percent, according to an
e-mailed note to clients.  Petrobras Argentina SA (PESA)  , a unit of Brazil’s
Petroleo Brasileiro SA and which also distributes fuel,
increased 4.6 percent to 6.81 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
